<br>
Very funny parody of dearly departed Sam K. and VI. It's funny, in the space of a single post you talked about two things which are dead.... 1) Sam K, and 2) Wizard Damage Dealing capacity to the extent they are group-friendly. <br>
<br>
You touched on the subject of when people notice there are &quot;issues&quot; with the Wiz Class in terms of damage. Many believe it's only post-50. I believe a quick study and someone who is observant can see the problems well before that. Make a line graph where you chart mana pool increases and then make another graph show damage/mana ratio's. Then, make a table where you express the &quot;time to contribute to group damage&quot; as expressed in mins\seconds of a wizard at a given level. Actually, if you are nimble in your abstract thought and arithmetic, you can work this out in your head and see the lines that should be correlated together....actually diverge. Also, the time to contribte to group stat goes down and you observe your increasingly downtime state at the upper levels. <br>
<br>
Of course, to be fair, few wizzies do full mana burns because of the wisdom of holding back for evacs and the like. But still the trends do not look good. Alot of wizard frustration no doubt comes from VI's profound inability to even notice these adverse trends. <br>
<br>
I just saw where the numbers were going. Retired at 26. Will come out of retirement when, if , damage is fixed. A person takes some flak for retiring early or disagreeing with the hypothesis that the wiz problems are exclusively post 50, BUT...I don't care. I'll be have my chanter to 40 a month before I would have had I leveled my wiz to 40 had I stuck it out. <br>
<br>
To each their own I guess....anyway, again, very comedic post....everyone needs one of those to lighten things every now and then!<br>
